About the DHHS Office of the Controller
The Office of the Controller sets and interprets all accounting and financial reporting policies and procedures for the Department as authorized by the rules and regulations of the Office of the State Controller and state statute, and executes all accounting transactions for DHHS.
Knowledge, Skills and Abilities / Competencies
To receive credit for all of your work history and credentials, you must list the information on the application form. Any information listed under the text resume section or on an attachment will not be considered for qualifying credit. Qualified applicants must document on the application that they possess all of the following:
Understanding of GAAP, government accounting methods and procedures needed to perform job duties;
Maintain proper internal controls and procedures in processing accounting transactions;
Knowledge to interpret financial information and apply departmental policies and procedures;
High level customer service skills and ability to communicate clearly in both written format and verbally.
Management prefers applicants with the following experience:
Work with various financial-related modules of the NCAS system, ie: Accounts Payable, Purchasing and General Ledger and/or a minimum of five years of an automated accounting system;
Working knowledge of XTND, Core Banking System (CB$) and E-procurement;
Demonstrated knowledge of Microsoft Word, Excel and other section software programs.
Minimum Education and Experience Requirements
Associate's Degree in Accounting from an appropriately accredited institution and two years of experience in accounting;
-OR-
High school diploma or General Educational Development (GED) diploma and three years of experience in accounting work;
-OR-
An equivalent combination of training and experience.
